N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 5001.11 - License fee

State Regulations
(a) A fee for a
license as an agent may be required in an amount determined by the commission
and is payable at the time of licensure. The fee is intended to cover the cost
of licensing and is not refundable. (b) A license renewal fee may be charged
annually in an amount determined by the commission. The fee is intended to
cover the cost of the licensing renewal operation and is not
refundable. Notes
